HTML?

HTML stands for Hyper Text Markup Language
HTML is the standard markup language for creating Web pages
HTML describes the structure of a Web page
HTML consists of a series of elements
HTML elements tell the browser how to display the content.

BASIC HTML DOCUMENT?

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Page Title</title>
</head>
<body>

<h1>My First Heading</h1>
<p>My first paragraph.</p>

</body>
</html>


<!DOCTYPE html> Its defines that this document is an HTML5 document
<html> root element of an HTML page
<head> contains meta information about the HTML page
<title> It specifies a title for the HTML page.
<body> defines the document's body, and is a container for all the visible contents, such as headings, paragraphs, images, hyperlinks, tables, lists, etc.
<h1> defines a large heading
<p> defines a paragraph

What is HTML element?

Its defined start tage, some content, end tag.

VOID ELEMENT OR EMPTY ELEMENT?

Some HTML elements have no content (like the <br> element). These elements are called empty elements. Empty elements do not have an end tag!

HTML BASICS
-----------

HTML headings
-------------
heading are defined <h1> to <h6> tags this has end tags also </h1> to </h6>.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h1>This is heading 1</h1>
<h2>This is heading 2</h2>
<h3>This is heading 3</h3>
<h4>This is heading 4</h4>
<h5>This is heading 5</h5>
<h6>This is heading 6</h6>

</body>
</html>

HTML paragraph
--------------
paragraphs are defined <p> tag this has end tag also </p>


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<p>This is paragraph one.</p>
<p>This is paragraph two.</p>

</body>
</html>

HTML links
----------
html links are defined <a> this also have end tag </a>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>HTML Links</h2>
<p>HTML links are defined with the a tag:</p>

<a href="https://github.com/balajim1999">This is my github link</a>

</body>
</html>

1. href is a attribute.
2. attributes are used give additional information about html element.

HTML image
----------
html images are defined <img> tag this has no end tag.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>HTML Images</h2>
<p>HTML images are defined with the img tag:</p>

<img src="linux.jpeg" alt="Linux image" width="104" height="142">

</body>
</html>

1. src,alt,width,height are attributes its gives additional information about <img> tag.
